name: temperature-salinity-and-extracted-chlorophyll-a-surface-data-collected-at-discrete-stations-du
notes: A Sea-Bird Electronics Conductivity, Temperature, Depth (CTD) instrument and a Sea-Bird Electronics Thermosalinograph (TSG) flow-through system were utilized during cruises conducted between January 1998 and August 2012 in South Florida coastal waters. These data are presented here in an Excel format (.xls).
